title: Pa. boys and girls: Plath, Hopkins help Little Flower end Ryan's streak
text:
Cailey Plath scored two minutes into the second half, after a series of back-and-forth passes with midfielder Casey Ritter.
Then the Sentinels settled in for 38 long minutes of preservation. 
Tess Hopkins led Little Flower's defense by neutralizing Archbishop Ryan star Jules Blank. 
Morgan Basileo delivered a six-save shutout. 
Archbishop Ryan is ranked No. 7 in Southeastern Pa. by The Inquirer. Boys' Soccer Matt Bachman scored three times as Abington stunned No. 9 Central Bucks South, 4-0, at home. Field Hockey Christen Pennington scored three minutes into overtime to give Neshaminy a 1-0 win at Council Rock North in the Suburban One Continental. Boys' Golf Methacton's Kyle Vance led with an 8-under-par 64 after Day 1 of the District 1 Class AAA tournament at Turtle Creek Golf Course in Royersford.
Quinn Guzman of Souderton finished second with a 69. Girls' Golf Maddie Sager of Owen J. Roberts shot 5-under 66 to take the lead after the first day of the District 1 Class AAA tournament at Gilbertsville Golf Club.
Coatesville's Samantha Staudt (68) and Council Rock North's Madeline Herr (69) were second and third.
